    type='think',
    think='Tests pass (60 tests, not 38 as PR description said - maybe the PR de
scription was from an earlier state or maybe some tests were added after). `flut
ter analyze` has no issues. `make arch-check` passes.\n\nNow let me check `make 
build` if possible. But the PR said `make mobile-build-apk` passed. Let me check
if there\'s a `make lint` command and try it.\n\nActually, I need to look at a f
ew more potential issues:\n\n1. **MatchingSwipeAnimation extends MatchingState**
- I flagged this as a potential Major issue. Let me think more carefully. Is it 
really a problem? The class is used as a field value, but it extends `MatchingSt
ate`. If someone accidentally does `emit(MatchingSwipeAnimation())`, the `BlocCo
nsumer` builder won\'t know how to handle it. But the current code never emits i
t directly. Is this really worth a Major? Let me reconsider. The PRD and flutter
.md talk about "BLoC 状态语义正确性" - a State class should reflect its business
semantic. `MatchingSwipeAnimation` doesn\'t represent a state of the matching fe
ature - it represents animation parameters. It should be a plain data class. I\'
ll keep this as Major.\n\n2. **Missing Widget Tests for LoginPage and HomePage**
- PRD US-SEP-1 AC #5 requires Widget Tests. The PR doesn\'t include them. Major.
\n\n3. **MatchingSocketCubit double emit** - I initially thought it was fine. Bu
t wait, in the `connect()` method:\n```dart\n_socketClient = (_clientFactory ?? 
MatchingSocketClient.new)(...);\n_socketClient?.connect();\nemit(const MatchingS
ocketConnected());\n```\nIf `_socketClient?.connect()` triggers the `onMatchCrea
ted` callback synchronously (unlikely in real socket, but possible in tests), th
e callback would emit `MatchingSocketMatchReceived` and then `MatchingSocketConn
ected` BEFORE the `emit(const MatchingSocketConnected())` at the end of `connect
()`. In that case, the stream would emit: MatchReceived, Connected (from callbac
k), Connected (from connect()). But the test expects Connected (from connect()) 
first. This is a race condition. However, in the actual `MatchingSocketClient`, 
`connect()` is likely async. The test uses a Mock where `connect()` does nothing
synchronously. So in production, the callback is async and won\'t fire during `c
onnect()`. This is probably fine.\n\nActually wait - looking at the test for `on
MatchCreated callback emits MatchReceived then Connected`:\n```dart\nawait cubit
.connect();\n// Trigger the callback that the cubit wired up to the client.\ncap
turedOnMatchCreated?.call(...);\nawait expectation;\n```\n\nThe test explicitly 
triggers the callback AFTER `await cubit.connect()`. So the callback fires after
`connect()` is done. The stream emits Connected (from connect()), then the test 
triggers the callback which emits MatchReceived then Connected. This matches the
expectation.\n\nIn production, `connect()` on a real socket is async, but the `a
wait` in `connect()` method only awaits `readAccessToken()`, not the socket conn
ection itself:\n```dart\nFuture<void> connect() async {\n  final token = await _
secureStorage.readAccessToken();\n  ...\n  _socketClient?.connect();\n  emit(con
st MatchingSocketConnected());\n}\n```\n\nSo `emit(const MatchingSocketConnected
())` happens immediately after starting the connection, not after the connection
is established. This is actually a semantic issue - the state says "Connected" b
efore the socket is actually connected. But this was the existing behavior (the 
original `HomePage._initSocket` also called `connect()` and didn\'t wait). So it
\'s not a new issue introduced by this PR.\n\n4. **Hardcoded duration value** - 
In `matching_bloc.dart`:\n```dart\nawait Future.delayed(DesignTokens.swipeFlyOut
Duration);\n```\nThis uses the new token. Good. But in `matching_socket_client.d
art`, the reconnection parameters are hardcoded:\n```dart\n\'reconnectionAttempt
s\': 5,\n\'reconnectionDelay\': 1000,\n\'reconnectionDelayMax\': 5000,\n```\nThe
flutter.md says:\n> 所有动画时长、缓动曲线必须统一从 `DesignTokens` 或 `Animatio
nTokens` 读取，禁止在业务代码中硬编码毫秒数\n\nBut these are socket configuratio
n parameters, not animation durations. And there\'s no existing token for socket
reconnection. I don\'t think this is a violation.\n\n5. **LoginCubit close()** -
In `login_cubit_test.dart`:\n```dart\ntest(\'cancels timer on close\', () {\n  f
akeAsync((async) {\n    cubit.startCountdown();\n    expect(cubit.state.countdow
n, 60);\n\n    cubit.close();\n    async.elapse(const Duration(seconds: 5));\n\n
   // After close, countdown should remain unchanged.\n    expect(cubit.state.co
untdown, 60);\n    expect(cubit.isClosed, isTrue);\n  });\n});\n```\n\nWait, `cu
bit.close()` returns a `Future<void>`. In `fakeAsync`, if you don\'t `await` it,
it might not complete before the assertions. But `fakeAsync` runs synchronously,
and since `close()` doesn\'t do any async work other than `super.close()` which 
is synchronous in bloc... Actually, `Cubit.close()` returns a Future but complet
